<div id="review_2805471402" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2805471402" />
    <a title="Daniel Simmons" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5904365-daniel-simmons"><img alt="Daniel Simmons" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1311864474p2/5904365.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2805471402?book_show_action=true">May 06, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Daniel Simmons" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Daniel Simmons" href="/user/show/5904365-daniel-simmons">Daniel Simmons</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2805471402" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7228185710776320390">An outstanding wartime and post-wartime dissection of Sri Lankan society. Though armed hostilities between the Sinhalese government and the Tamil Tigers may officially have ended, a toxic brew of political, religious, and linguistic conflicts still simmers beneath the surface and occasionally bursts anew into view. A disheartening and necessary read for anyone with interest in this beautiful but conflict-torn region.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

