<div id="review_3791680195" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3791680195" />
    <a title="Keerthi Kiran" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28031539-keerthi-kiran"><img alt="Keerthi Kiran" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1390643226p2/28031539.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3791680195?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Keerthi Kiran" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Keerthi Kiran" href="/user/show/28031539-keerthi-kiran">Keerthi Kiran</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3791680195" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8889266991938570332">The book is a poignant narrative of Sri Lankan civil war. The book has stories of Tamil people with wide array of affiliations and details the impact of war on its people, society and the country. The book highlights the impact of democracy on a multi-ethnic society. The frame of reference shifting to a lens of majority and minority. The role of government in shaping system in a resource constrained job/opportunity market - changing entrance criteria, introducing language criteria to further the</span>
  <span id="freeText8889266991938570332" style="display:none">The book is a poignant narrative of Sri Lankan civil war. The book has stories of Tamil people with wide array of affiliations and details the impact of war on its people, society and the country. The book highlights the impact of democracy on a multi-ethnic society. The frame of reference shifting to a lens of majority and minority. The role of government in shaping system in a resource constrained job/opportunity market - changing entrance criteria, introducing language criteria to further the opportunity for majority population at the cost of minority groups. Another thread covered the impacts of systemic suppression on self-worth, attraction to violent autocrats. The books also shows the perpetual cycle that violence perpetuates. While the setting for this book is Sri Lanka, this book’s underlying themes are relevant to all young democracies with multi-ethnic, cultural and religious fabric. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8889266991938570332" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


